name: Vaccine-Rabies
description: Give at 0, 3, 7, 14, 28 days after bite.  Watching animal if domesticated.  If no disease in animal after 10 days, the 14 and 28 day doses are optional.

name: Vaccine-Tetanus toxoid(TD)
description: Give for all wounds if <3 doses vaccine previously given.  Give for clean/minor wounds if >3 doses. and last dose > 10 years ago.  Give for dirty/major wounds if >3 doses received and last dose >10 years ago.  Give TD to all pregnant women (2 doses, 4 weeks apart)

name: Vaccine-DPT
description: Give at 6, 10 and 14 weeks of age

name: Vaccine-BCG
description: Give at birth or on first contact

name: Vaccine-OPV
description: Give at 6, 10 and 14 weeks of age

name: Vaccine-PCV
description: Give at 6 weeks, 10 weeks and 9 months

name: Vaccine-Measles/rubella
description: Give at 9 and 15 months of age

name: Vaccine-JE
description: Give at 12-23 months in high risk districts
